      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "NERANO NZ (5) has been racing well against good company at this circuit and distance, recording back-to-back seconds from wider barriers than this before finishing 5m away last time. Should be at his peak now and looks well placed. Stablemate CATCHAFIRE NZ (4) faded to midfield as favourite in his last outing three weeks ago but is better than that having scored a win at this circuit and distance three back. Worth another chance. THALASSOPHOBIA (3) enjoys a drop in grade from the Riverina Championships and went into that series off a win at this venue. Draws for a good showing. ALTA WILLIAM (9) did a good job from a similar barrier last time when he raced parked but stuck on to be beaten only 3.7m. HUGO MAGUIRE NZ (2) continued his good form with a last-start win in the Autumn Gift and draws to be competitive again.",
